  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Your Local Energy Team</h2>
      <p>
        When you work with EES, you're not dealing with a call centre or a sales team that disappears after the contract is signed. You're working with the same local team from first consultation through to installation and ongoing support.
      </p>
      <p>
        We're based at 13 Nobility Street, Moolap — and we service Greater Geelong, Torquay, the Surf Coast, Bellarine Peninsula, Golden Plains, and wider regional Victoria.
      </p>

      <h2>What Our Team Does</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>System design</strong> — we assess your property, review your energy usage, and design integrated systems tailored to your home or building</li>
        <li><strong>Installation</strong> — our CEC-accredited electricians install every system. No subcontractors, no third-party handoffs</li>
        <li><strong>Commissioning</strong> — we commission and test every installation, walk you through the monitoring, and make sure everything is working correctly</li>
        <li><strong>Ongoing support</strong> — if something needs attention after installation, you call us directly. We're local and we're here for the long term</li>
        <li><strong>Research and development</strong> — our <a href="/laboratory/research-team">research team</a> designs, builds, and tests products at our <a href="/laboratory/facility">Geelong facility</a> before they go into homes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Accreditations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>CEC Accredited Installer</strong> — Clean Energy Council accredited for solar design and installation</li>
        <li><strong>Solar Victoria Approved Retailer</strong> — authorised to process Victorian Government solar and battery rebates</li>
        <li><strong>SAI Approved Retailer</strong> — Solar Accreditation Initiative approved</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why It Matters</h2>
      <p>
        Most solar companies use subcontractors — your system is designed by one company, sold by another, and installed by a third. If something goes wrong, nobody takes ownership.
      </p>
      <p>
        At EES, the person who designs your system works with the person who installs it. Our <strong>10-year workmanship warranty</strong> means we stand behind every installation, and because we're local, we're down the road if you need us.
      </p>

